main event: Two lights were observed in the sky over Greenville, Ohio, on March 25, 1964.
interesting points: The lights were seen about 3 fingers above the western horizon,They appeared to be the size of dimes and blinked slowly for a duration of 30 minutes,The sighting was reported by a civilian source,The witness had reported the lights at approximately 2355L,The investigation concluded that the lights were likely Venus and Jupiter.
sighted object: two blinking lights in the sky
witness description: a civilian who observed the lights
